# Webspace testing (Seismo 0.5)

The 0.5 consolidation is **validated on the user's actual webspace**, not only locally. Each slice ends with an upload + live smoke test before the next slice starts.

## Hard rules

- **0.4 keeps running as the reference.** On the user's host the actual layout is **0.5 at `/seismo/`** (the stable, user-facing URL) and **0.4 at `/seismo-staging/`** (the living fallback). Never touch `/seismo-staging/` from 0.5 work — it exists so we can diff live behaviour against the new code at any time.
- **No destructive DB operations** in any slice that ships to the shared host, unless the user has explicitly confirmed a backup or a dedicated test DB. Read-only slices may point at the existing 0.4 DB; schema-changing slices MUST use a fresh DB or an explicit, reversible migration.
- **`config.local.php` is created on the server**, never committed, never uploaded with real credentials from the dev machine. Ship the `.example` file; the user (or wizard) fills it in on the host.
- **No FTP automation by the agent.** The agent prepares a concrete, copy-pasteable upload list per slice and the user performs the upload. Never assume a deploy path that hasn't been confirmed.

## What every slice must produce

1. A **one-line test URL** the user can open (e.g. `https://<host>/seismo_0.5/?action=health`).
2. A **checklist of expected output** for that URL (dbStatus ok, schema version, mode, etc.).
3. An **upload list** showing exactly which files/folders to transfer, and which to skip (`.git`, `.cursor`, most of `docs/` except **always** `docs/db-schema.sql` when `migrate.php` is part of the slice — the migrator reads it at runtime).
4. A **rollback note**: what the user does if the slice misbehaves (usually "delete `/seismo_0.5/`; 0.4 is untouched").

## Portability bugs found on the webspace

When something breaks on the host but works locally (path, header, PHP extension, mod_rewrite, session dir, …):

1. Fix it in 0.5 directly (don't re-exile it to 0.4).
2. **Append** the finding to `docs/setup-wizard-notes.md` so the future first-run wizard catches it.
3. If it affects 0.4 too, mirror the fix there with a short commit; don't leave the user on a broken mothership while 0.5 matures.

## Slice → URL map (updated as we go)

User's host: `hektopascal.org`. 0.5 test URLs are relative to `https://www.hektopascal.org/seismo/`.

- **Slice 0 (skeleton):** `?action=health` — ✅ verified live (PHP 8.2.30, MariaDB 10.6.20, schema 17, mothership, base path `/seismo`). **Migrations without CLI:** set `SEISMO_MIGRATE_KEY` in `config.local.php`, then open `?action=migrate&key=…` once — plain-text response; no SSH required.
- **Slice 1 (read-only dashboard):** `?action=index` — renders existing entries via the new `EntryRepository` using `dashboard_entry_loop.php`. Upload list: `src/Controller/DashboardController.php`, `src/Repository/EntryRepository.php`, `views/index.php`, `views/helpers.php`, `views/partials/dashboard_entry_loop.php`, `assets/css/style.css`, and the updated `index.php`. Expected: newest-first timeline of up to 30 entries, Magnitu score badges where scored, no filter UI, no refresh button, no star buttons (favourite POST route returns in a later slice). Rollback: re-upload only the Slice 0 `index.php` (which sets the default to `health`) — no DB changes in this slice.
- **Slice 1.5 (search + favourites + star toggle):** Same base URL; add `?q=test`, `?view=favourites`, and POST `toggle_favourite` via the ☆/★ control. Upload: also `src/Repository/EntryFavouriteRepository.php`, `src/Controller/FavouriteController.php`, and the updated `EntryRepository.php`, `DashboardController.php`, `views/index.php`, `index.php` (router). Expected: search filters merged timeline; favourites view lists starred entries; star toggles `entry_favourites` locally and redirects back. No tag pills yet (Slice 4).
- **Slice 5 (Magnitu API + read-only export):** Schema **20**.
  - `?action=migrate&key=…` — expect "Applying migration to version 20" (one-time).
  - `curl -H 'Authorization: Bearer <api_key>' https://www.hektopascal.org/seismo/?action=magnitu_status` — JSON with entry/score counts, Leg excluded.
  - `curl -H 'Authorization: Bearer <api_key>' 'https://www.hektopascal.org/seismo/?action=magnitu_entries&type=feed_item&limit=5'` — same shape Magnitu's `sync.py` consumes in 0.4.
  - `curl -H 'Authorization: Bearer <export:api_key>' 'https://www.hektopascal.org/seismo/?action=export_briefing&since=2026-04-01'` — Markdown digest; default labels are `investigation_lead,important`.
  - `curl -H 'Authorization: Bearer <export:api_key>' 'https://www.hektopascal.org/seismo/?action=export_entries&limit=10'` — JSON with entries + `score` block.
  - **Negative tests (two-key model):** Magnitu `api_key` on `export_*` must 401; export `export:api_key` on `magnitu_*` must 401.
  - **Operator setup:** generate `export:api_key` once (`php -r "echo bin2hex(random_bytes(24));"`) and store via SQL or the future Settings UI (Slice 6). Migration 004 seeds an empty row so validators see "not configured" until you do.
  - **Rollback:** revert the new files; no entry-source schema touched. `entry_scores` row precedence (Magnitu beats recipe) is identical to 0.4, so mixed-version staging is safe.
